quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  21,76,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Noah had cried out to Us earlier, so We responded to him and delivered him and his family¬†from the great distress"
  21,77,"And We made him prevail over those who had rejected Our signs. They were truly an evil people, so We drowned them all"
  21,78,"And ňĻrememberňļ when David and Solomon passed judgment regarding the crops ruined ňĻat nightňļ by someone‚Äôs sheep, and We were witness to their judgments"
  21,79,"We guided ňĻyoungňļ Solomon to a fairer settlement,¬†and granted each of them wisdom and knowledge. We subjected the mountains as well as the birds to hymn ňĻOur praisesňļ along with David. It is We Who did ňĻit allňļ"
  21,80,We taught him the art of making body armour to protect you in battle. Will you then be grateful
  21,81,"And to Solomon We subjected the raging winds, blowing by his command to the land We had showered with blessings. It is We Who know everything"
  21,82,"And ňĻWe subjectedňļ some jinn¬†that dived for him,¬†and performed other duties. It is We Who kept them in check"
  21,83,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Job cried out to his Lord, ‚ÄúI have been touched with adversity,¬†and You are the Most Merciful of the merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  21,84,"So We answered his prayer and removed his adversity, and gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for the ňĻdevotedňļ worshippers"
  21,85,"And ňĻrememberňļ Ishmael, Enoch, and ‚Īęul-Kifl.¬†They were all steadfast"
  21,86,"We admitted them into Our mercy, for they were truly of the righteous"
  21,87,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the Man of the Whale stormed off ňĻfrom his cityňļ in a rage, thinking We would not restrain him.¬†Then in the ňĻveils ofňļ darkness¬†he cried out, ‚ÄúThere is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except You. Glory be to You! I have certainly done wrong.‚ÄĚ"
  21,88,So We answered his prayer and rescued him from anguish. And so do We save the ňĻtrueňļ believers
  21,89,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Zachariah cried out to his Lord, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Do not leave me childless, though You are the Best of Successors.‚ÄĚ"
  21,90,"So We answered his prayer, granted him John, and made his wife fertile. Indeed, they used to race in doing good, and call upon Us with hope and fear, totally humbling themselves before Us"
  21,91,"And ňĻrememberňļ the one who guarded her chastity, so We breathed into her through Our angel, ňĻGabriel,ňļ¬†making her and her son a sign for all peoples"
  21,92,"ňĻO prophets!ňļ Indeed, this religion of yours is ňĻonlyňļ one, and I am your Lord, so worship Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  21,93,Yet the people have divided it into sects. But to Us they will all return